                <div class="faq">

                    <p class="header">Frequently Asked Questions</p>

                    <p class="question">I send a message and not everyone received it, what went wrong?</p>

                    <p class="answer">
                        The addon can send messages along a path made up by Battle.net friend connections and guild channels. When
                        you send a message, it will be received by anyone that can be reached through a combination of Battle.net
                        friend connections and guild channels. Everyone on these paths, must have the addon installed as well.
                    </p>
                    <p class="answer">
                        Let's assume we have Legolas, Shania and Mirgo playing the game. Legolas and Shania are Battle.net friends.
                        Legolas is not in a guild but Shania and Mirgo are both in "Awesome Raiders" on Darkmoon Faire. All three have
                        QLTalk installed and enabled. When Legolas sends a message using the addon, Shania and Mirgo wil receive it.
                    </p>
                    <p class="answer">
                        But if Shania would not have the addon installed or enabled, neither Shania nor Mirgo will receive the message
                        send by Legolas. Even though Mirgo has the addon installed, there is no path of Battle.net friends and guilds
                        between Mirgo and Legolas where every intermediate player has QLTalk installed and enabled.
                    </p>
                    <p class="answer">
                        So depending on who is online and what Battle.net friends they have, your message may be missed by some and you
                        may miss some messages send by others.
                    </p>
                    <p class="answer">
                        The more members of a Danse Macabre have the addon installed, the less likely it wil be you miss messages!
                    </p>

                    <p class="question">Why isn't the addon available on Curse.com?</p>

                    <p class="answer">
                        Having the addon available on Curse.com would make installing and keeping it up to date much easier. Sadly,
                        due to the way the addon works, it is currently not a good idea to have it installed on a wide basis. In
                        other words, we have to keep it limited to La Danse Macabre members. By making the addon available on Curse.com
                        we can't guarantee this.
                    </p>
                    <p class="answer">
                        Future versions of the addon may be released on Curse.com. So stay tuned!
                    </p>

                    <p class="question">Is the addon safe to use? Does it conform to Blizzard's EULA?</p>

                    <p class="answer">
                        As far was we know, this addon is safe to use and does not violate Blizzard's terms.
                    </p>

